'''Sipie''' (pronounced SY PIE, like ''Sirius Python'') is a computer program written by Eli Criffield for the  of  stations. The program is written in , and can use , , or  to play the streams. Sipie is developed on, and mainly used in Linux but should work on any platform that a python interpreter is available. Originally, Sipie was only usable through a  but a small lightweight  is now included.
Sirius Satellite Radio subscribers who use a Linux-based operating system or would like an alternative to sirius.com's online player can use Sipie to login and stream on-line channels, neither Windows Media Player ''nor'' a web browser are needed.